One hundred years ago, a group of women proposed the Equal Rights Amendment (ERA) to guarantee gender equality in the Constitution. Now, the fight to codify women's rights and gender equality continues. The author has long supported the ERA and believes it is time to make it the law of the land. They emphasize that no one should face discrimination based on their sex and urge Congress to recognize ratification of the ERA. The author believes that all Americans should have equal rights and protections under the law.